name: wire tree origami crane, silver plated copper wire and origami paper cranes
description:
A small wire tree, perfect for home decoration.
A special tree, dedicated to Japan, one year after the earthquake and the tsunami (11 March 2011). Origami crane folding is a symbolic way to pray for the victims of that disaster. I hand fold the paper cranes, so no one is exactly the same with the other.

Made out of non-tarnish silver plated copper wire and origami paper cranes. 

** Base is not included **

Number of brunches: 40
Approximate dimensions in cm: 6,5 cm x 7 cm (2,5 in x 2,75 in)

Origami crane is the symbol of hope, peace and health. You can find more info about the origami crane folding and its meaning here, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thousand_origami_cranes

I make every tree to order so the tree you receive may not be exactly the tree pictured. If you require a picture of your tree before I ship it I will be more than happy to send one. Please allow up to 10 days for the creation and delivery of your tree.
